                <p id="ethan-bio__text" class="bio__text">(As of December 2021) Ethan Balcik is a senior at The Pennsylvania State University's Schreyer Honors College studying Information Sciences and Technology, and Mathematics.  His research interests include information theory, coding theory, quantum computation, graph theory, combinatorics, and analysis.  Ethan is currently working on his senior thesis on the applications and performance of partial replication and erasure coding in distributed key-value stores.  Upon his graduation, Ethan will join IBM as a DevOps engineer working on the CloudPak for Multicloud Management development and release pipelines.</p>
